1. How many types of conditions are available in conditional formatting on Excel?
There are 5 types of conditions are available in conditional formatting on Excel are:
   a. Highlight Cells Rules
   b. Top/Bottom Rules
   c. Data Bars
   d. Color Scales
   e. Icon Sets

2. How to insert border in Excel with Format Cells dialog?
Step-1- Select one or more cells to which you'd like to add borders.

Step-2- Open the Format Cells dialog box by doing one of the following:
Click the down arrow next to the Borders button, and then click More Borders at the bottom of the drop-down list.
Right click the selected cells and choose Format Cellsâ€¦ from the context menu.
Press Ctrl+1 shortcut.

Step-3- In the Format Cells dialog box, switch to the Border tab and choose the line style and color first.

Step-4- When done, click OK.

3. How to Format Numbers as Currency in Excel?
Step-1- Right Click any one of the top of the column.
Step-2- Go to Format Cells > Number > Currency.

4. What are the steps to format numbers in Excel with the Percent style?
Step-1- Right Click any one of the top of the column.
Step-2- Go to Format Cells > Number > Percentage.

5. What is a shortcut to merge two or more cells in excel?
The shortcut to merge two or more cells in excel is: ALT H+M+M.

6. How do you use text commands in Excel?
Step-1- Right Click any one of the top of the column.
Step-2- Go to Format Cells > Number > Text.


